    <p>
        This site was published in the fall of 2016 in <a rel="external noopener" href="http://www.somervillema.gov/">Somerville, Massachusetts</a>. It was built on a Mid 2014 Mac&#8202;Book Pro using <a rel="external noopener" href="https://github.com/ericwbailey/enchilada">enchilada, a personal project boilerplate</a>. More information is available in this site's <a rel="external noopener" href="https://github.com/ericwbailey/ericbailey.design/blob/master/source/humans.txt"><code class="no-letter-break">humans.txt</code> file</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
        The site is set in <a rel="external noopener" href="https://typekit.com/fonts/abril/details/abril-text-regular">Abril</a>, an editorial typeface inspired by nineteenth century Slab Serif and Scotch Roman type. Abril was made by the Czech foundry <a rel="external noopener" href="http://www.type-together.com/">Type Together</a>, and (begrudgingly) hosted by <a rel="external noopener" href="https://typekit.com/">Typekit</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
        The site's code is <a rel="external noopener" href="https://pages.github.com/">hosted on Git&#8202;Hub</a>, with a <a rel="external noopener" href="https://iwantmyname.com/">domain name provided by iwantmyname</a>. Site elements are built using relative-sized units set to a <a rel="external noopener" href="http://type-scale.com/?size=16&scale=1.333&text=A%20Visual%20Type%20Scale&webfont=Libre+Baskerville&font-family=%27Libre%20Baskerville%27,%20serif&font-weight=400&font-family-headers=&font-weight-headers=inherit&background-color=white&font-color=%23333">Perfect Fourth modular scale</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
